  "prompt": "How to convert fractions to whole numbers?",
  "response": "To convert fractions to whole numbers, follow these steps:\n\n1. If the numerator is divisible by the denominator:\n   - Divide the numerator by the denominator\n   - The result will be a whole number\n\nExamples:\n- 4/2 = 2\n- 6/3 = 2\n- 8/4 = 2\n\n2. If the numerator is not divisible by the denominator:\n   - You'll need to round the result\n   - Divide the numerator by the denominator\n   - Choose rounding method:\n     a) Round to nearest whole number\n     b) Round down (floor)\n     c) Round up (ceiling)\n\nExamples:\n- 5/2 = 2.5\n   - Rounded to nearest: 3\n   - Rounded down: 2\n   - Rounded up: 3\n\n3. For mixed numbers:\n   - The whole number part is already a whole number\n   - Convert the fractional part as described above\n\nExample:\n- 3 1/2\n   - Whole number part: 3\n   - Fractional part: 1/2 (rounded to 1)\n   - Result could be 3 or 4 depending on rounding method\n\nChoose the rounding method based on your specific requirements.",
